oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Ocoee Street
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: View of Ocoee Street located between 6th and 8th. A boy is riding in his pony cart down the street. House on left belonged to George L. Hardwick, Sr. (1861-1940), a Mill Executive at the Cleveland Woolen Mills, and the home next to it belonged to Clung May. The First Presbyterian Church is behind the house visible on right with porch and picket fence.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mules; Streets; Carriages & coaches
